aa9e0be9e6ca.title: Outside of the two INTs, let’s not forget the fumble on OSU’s 2-yard line.

paragraphs.text: Outside of the two INTs, let’s not forget the fumble on OSU’s 2-yard line. You simply can’t have three turnovers that deep in either territory and expect a victory.
paragraphs.name: 549d

2bb3d4a85da4.title: The refs missed a pretty clear DPI against OSU early in the game.

paragraphs.text: The refs missed a pretty clear DPI against OSU early in the game. Besides that, the officiating was pretty even. OSU got an either-or call with the ball spot; it really could’ve gone either way with the spot. Some games OSU gets the calls and some games UM will get the calls. This game was not egregious, so the refs did not decide it.

paragraphs.text: I’m an MSU fan that hoped both teams would lose (I don’t care that this was impossible) and I got my wish. My view? OSU got multiple breaks, & still required 2 OT to beat UM. I thought UM looked like the better team most of the game, but Speights’ 2 picks crushed their hopes. I hope UW wins the PAC-12 & makes the argument moot
